# How css is rendered

1. Browser loads the HTML
2. Converts HTML to the DOM
3. Fetched linked resources
4. Browser parses css
5. Render tree is laid out
6. UI is printed

Terminology + Core Concepts

- replaced element
- non-replaced element

# SELECTORS

- selects the HTML element or elements you want tp apply some styles to.

1. Type Selectors
   h1{
   color:red;
   }

2. Class Selectors
   .title{
   color:red;
   }

3. ID selector
   #title{
   color:red;
   }

4. Universal Selector
   \*{
   color:red
   }

5. Combining Selectors
   .body p{
   color:pink;
   }

.body p#blue{
color:blue;
} color all the paragraph element with the ID blue inside of a class element body

# Specificity - specificity_calculartor

               algo used by the browser to determine which css declaration should be applied

# Inline Styles -

               have higher specificity than ID selectors. They overwrite IDs.
               <p id ="text" stlye="color:blue">Lorem Ipsum</p>   #text{color:red}

# Foundation

1. Color
   > i. Named Color : blue,red,orange
   > ii. Hexadecimal : #0000FF
   > iii. RGB : rgb(31,120,50)
   > iv. RGBA : rgba(255,255,255,.5)
   > v. HSL : hsl(50 80% 40%)

